Ships and rescue teams scoured rough seas off Indonesia for hundreds of people still missing after a ferry disaster off Central Java navy commander Colonel Yan Simamora island , as more weary survivors were plucked to safety . 
Bad weather on Tuesday prevented search aircraft from looking for more survivors from an Indonesian ferry that sank in stormy weather as 400 people remained missing days after the disaster . 
The ferry was en route from Kumai on Borneo island to the Javanese port city of Semarang when it sank . 
Search teams said by late Monday about 100 bodies had been recovered . 